  "texts": [
    "In the future, it would be interesting to study the heterogeneity of mechanisms behind the exploration behavior.We assumed stable categories of exploiters and explorers using the full trajectory of researchers, yet there can be variation throughout their career.",
    "For example, we observed aging patterns within trajectories, with MSD of explorers and exploiters showing similar values within the first 5 years after their first publication, after which MSD values for explorers are significantly larger (Fig. 4c, Fig.",
    "S11 in Additional file 1).",
    "This could indicate that explorers go through two phases: a first phase where they are staying within a few most visited locations, followed by an exploratory behaviour towards other locations.",
    "Such a behavior could be formally captured using the concept of \"intermittent behavior\" from stochastic processes [60]."
  ],
